# Stack Constraints

- Use only project-approved stack: Next.js frontend, NestJS backend, Prisma + PostgreSQL, Docker Compose local runtime.
- Keep TypeScript-first implementations; avoid introducing plain JavaScript where TypeScript exists.
- Reuse existing libs before adding new dependencies.
- Keep API paths under `/api` unless explicitly documented otherwise (for example `/metrics`).
- Preserve local-first developer workflow (`docker compose up -d`).
- Document new infrastructure services in `README.md` when user-facing.
